article.description: North Florida collects fourth straight win, 63-56
article.headline: North Florida collects fourth straight win, 63-56
article.linkText: North Florida collects fourth straight win, 63-56
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. -- Jalen Nesbitt led four North Florida players in double figures with 14 points and the Ospreys won their fourth straight game with a 63-56 victory over Bethune-Cookman on Wednesday night. Chris Davenport added 13 points, Trent Mackey 12 and Romelo Banks 10 for the Ospreys (5-3). Delino Dear, a transfer from Toledo, matched career highs with 19 points and 12 rebounds for the Wildcats (2-6). Clemmye Owens added 12 points. The Ospreys led by three at halftime and built their lead to 12 with 14:32 remaining in the game. The Wildcats followed with an 8-0 run while the Ospreys endured a scoring drought of more than 5 minutes. Owen's 3-pointer closed the gap to 53-50 with 3:13 left but the Ospreys responded with four points from Nesbitt and a 3-pointer from Mackey to go up 10 with 1:13 left. The victory was the 250th for the North Florida program.
